	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />When I went to Akihabara today, I saw this:  <a href="http://tinycartridge.com/post/59371579/new-portable-famicom-with-a-psp-esque-design" class="postlink">link</a>
<br />
<br />It's a portable famicom, sold for about 5000 yen.  As anybody tried it?  I guess it must be based on some kind of famiclone or something.  
<br />
<br />They had for demo paper boy and the screen seemed fine. Cannot tell about the rest (sound, buttons etc).  Almost feel like buying one but still, if it just a clone, there is a good chance that many games won't work anyway.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
