	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What about those blatantly illegal consoles which include XX-in-one rom chips?  Like the OneStation, available for $40 with free shipping.  The cartridge for that system is a self contained NES, mapper, and flash rom chip containing lots of games, and not just mapper 0 games.  The cartridge pins output an audio and video signal and take in buttons and power.  Some get the sound duty cycles wrong.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


